# Namma-Mistri - Mock API & Data Structure Documentation

This document outlines the data structure used for simulating worker, booking, and feedback data in the Namma-Mistri application.

## 1. Worker Entity Structure

The worker details are stored locally using Room Database or Firebase and initialized in `NammaMistriApplication.kt`.

| Field                | Type    | Description                                             |
| :------------------- | :------ | :------------------------------------------------------ |
| `workerId`           | String  | Unique identifier for the worker (e.g., "WRK-001")      |
| `name`               | String  | Name of the worker                                      |
| `profession`         | String  | Worker category (Electrician, Plumber, Carpenter, etc.) |
| `experience`         | Int     | Years of experience                                     |
| `phoneNumber`        | String  | Contact number of the worker                            |
| `address`            | String  | Worker location/address                                 |
| `availabilityStatus` | Boolean | Availability status of the worker                       |
| `rating`             | Float   | Average customer rating                                 |
| `serviceCharge`      | String  | Estimated service cost                                  |
| `profileImageUrl`    | String  | URL of worker profile image                             |
| `description`        | String  | Brief description of worker skills                      |

---

## 2. Booking Entity Structure

This structure handles customer booking details for different services.

| Field             | Type   | Description                                                 |
| :---------------- | :----- | :---------------------------------------------------------- |
| `bookingId`       | String | Unique booking identifier                                   |
| `customerName`    | String | Name of the customer                                        |
| `workerId`        | String | ID of the booked worker                                     |
| `serviceType`     | String | Type of requested service                                   |
| `bookingDate`     | String | Selected booking date                                       |
| `bookingTime`     | String | Selected booking time                                       |
| `bookingStatus`   | String | Status of booking (Pending, Accepted, Completed, Cancelled) |
| `customerAddress` | String | Address for the service                                     |
| `customerPhone`   | String | Customer contact number                                     |

---

## 3. Feedback & Review Entity Structure

This structure stores customer ratings and service reviews.

| Field           | Type   | Description                             |
| :-------------- | :----- | :-------------------------------------- |
| `feedbackId`    | Int    | Auto-generated primary key              |
| `workerId`      | String | ID of the worker receiving feedback     |
| `customerName`  | String | Name of the customer                    |
| `rating`        | Int    | Customer rating (1 to 5 stars)          |
| `reviewMessage` | String | Review or feedback message              |
| `timestamp`     | Long   | System time when feedback was submitted |

---

## 4. Localization Strategy

The application is designed to support multilingual functionality using Android string resources for future expansion.

* **Default Language:** English

* **Planned Languages:** Kannada, Hindi, Tamil, Telugu

* **Example JSON Representation (Mocked):**

```json
{
  "workerId": "WRK-001",
  "name": "Ramesh",
  "profession": "Electrician",
  "experience": 5,
  "rating": 4.5,
  "availabilityStatus": true
}
```

---

## 5. Implementation Details

* **Database:** Android Room Persistence Library / Firebase Realtime Database
* **Initialization:** Mock worker and booking data are pre-populated in `NammaMistriApplication.onCreate()` to simulate API responses.
* **Authentication:** Firebase Authentication
* **Images:** Loaded dynamically using Coil or Glide from external image URLs.
* **Offline Support:** Room Database caching enables offline data access.
* **Architecture:** MVVM (Model-View-ViewModel)
* **Asynchronous Operations:** Kotlin Coroutines and StateFlow for reactive updates.
